:INFO
What Vermicomposting Produces
Red wigglers (Eisenia fetida) process organic kitchen waste into worm castings, one \
of the most nutrient-dense soil amendments available. A mature bin with 500 g of \
worms processes roughly 250 g of food scraps per day. The finished castings improve \
soil structure, water retention, and microbial life far beyond what standard compost \
achieves.

:COUNTER.half
500 Grams
Starting worm weight for a small bin
|
4 to 6 Weeks
Time to first usable castings

